&gt; ELSE EVER AGAIN!&quot;
&gt;
&gt; With his last words he throws out a thunderous roar.  His pace quickens upon
&gt; approach of the portal.  He also hoped that if there was anyone on the other
&gt; side that his voice carried through to the other side, as he roars once
&gt; again with even stronger magnitude.

&lt;NEW&gt;

TUSCON&#39;s roar echoed everywhere! Even the walls and floor seemed to
resonate with the sound of it!

Having approached the portal, TUSCON was standing inside a room
looking at what appeared to be a door way. However instead of it being
constructed of iron and steel it was composed of energy. It appeared
similar in construction the one that he himself had went through when
he was being brought into this base.

The room itself was fairly non descriptive, basic gun metal grey
walls, a few monitors and consoles around the room and, besides the
door that TUSCON entered, there were two others. Other than that the
room was barren and quiet, only the slight humming from the portal
could be heard.

BIG CONVOY, BREAK and MACH KICK entered slowly behind TUSCON their
weapons out as they watched TUSCON&#39;s back.

&quot;There are more guards approaching your position.&quot; LONG RACK said over
their comlink. &quot;What ever you&#39;re going to do you&#39;d better do it
quick.&quot;

&quot;How many?&quot; BIG CONVOY said.

&quot;All of them?&quot; LONG RACK came back. Of course that was probably an
overstatement, but one can gather that a lot of SHARKTICONS were about
to rush through the door soon. However the alarms were still going
off.

CONVOY looked over at TUSCON, &quot;Seems like we got a choice to make. We
can face the fire here, or we can take our chances through that.&quot; He
pointed at the portal.

Niether choice seemed to be a good one. Not even TUSCON or BIG CONVOY
could stand against MAGMATRON&#39;s full forces, especially if MAGMATRON
himself showed up.

